ASL Numbers Guide (1-100)

Basic Numbers (1-10):
1 - Point index finger up
2 - Point index and middle finger up
3 - Point index, middle, and ring fingers up
4 - Point all fingers except thumb up
5 - Hold all fingers up
6 - Touch thumb to pinky, other fingers up
7 - Touch thumb to ring finger, other fingers up
8 - Touch thumb to middle finger, other fingers up
9 - Touch thumb to index finger, other fingers up
10 - Make a fist with thumb up

Teens (11-19):
11 - Point index finger up, then point index finger up again
12 - Point index finger up, then point index and middle finger up
(Continue pattern...)

Tens (20, 30, 40, etc.):
20 - Point index and middle finger up, then make a fist
30 - Point index, middle, and ring fingers up, then make a fist
(Continue pattern...)

Practice counting regularly to improve speed and accuracy!